# Tool Stack

How each tool connects in the Acme Consulting GTM system.

## Core Tools

### Clay
**Purpose:** Lead enrichment, signal detection, scoring, and outbound email sequencing.
**Role in system:** The central hub for prospect data. Raw leads go in, enriched and scored leads come out. Also handles email campaign execution via Clay Sequencer.

**What flows through Clay:**
- Lead import (CSV from Sales Navigator, HubSpot, or manual entry)
- AI enrichment (Claygent prompts for signal detection)
- Lead scoring (multi-dimensional rubric)
- Copy generation (founder-voice emails and LinkedIn messages)
- QA validation (automated quality checks on generated copy)
- Email sending (Clay Sequencer for automated cadence)

**Key integration points:**
- Imports from Sales Navigator exports and HubSpot
- Sends emails via SMTP (founder@acme-consulting.com)
- Exports to Google Sheets for analysis
- Pairs with HeyReach for LinkedIn automation

### HeyReach
**Purpose:** LinkedIn automation (connection requests, DMs).
**Role in system:** Executes LinkedIn outreach in parallel with email sequences from Clay. Tracks connection acceptance, replies, and profile views.

**Integration with Clay:**
- Pulls LinkedIn connection message text from Clay table
- Reports engagement back (webhook or manual sync)
- When LinkedIn engagement detected, Clay pauses email sequence

### Sales Navigator
**Purpose:** Prospect identification and list building.
**Role in system:** Source of raw lead lists. Filtered by title, company size, seniority, and activity level before export to Clay.

### HubSpot
**Purpose:** CRM (historical). Some existing lead data lives here.
**Role in system:** Legacy data source. Leads originally enriched here are migrated to Clay for active campaigns.

### Google Sheets
**Purpose:** Analysis, reporting, and sharing with the founder.
**Role in system:** Secondary analysis layer. Weekly exports from Clay for pivot table analysis (which signals correlate with engagement, which angles work best).

### Google Drive
**Purpose:** Client deliverable sharing.
**Role in system:** Finished deliverables (proposals, briefs, research summaries) are exported from this vault, cleaned, converted to DOCX, and placed in the shared Google Drive folder for the founder.

### Obsidian (This Vault)
**Purpose:** Source of truth for context, playbooks, and entity management.
**Role in system:** All company knowledge, process documentation, and deal tracking lives here. Claude Code reads this vault before generating any outreach or deliverables.

### Claude Code
**Purpose:** AI assistant for research, content generation, and pipeline management.
**Role in system:** Reads vault context, generates research briefs, writes outreach copy, scores leads, manages deal progression. Operates within the RevLoop framework.

## Data Flow

```
Sales Navigator / HubSpot / Manual
        |
        v
    Clay (import)
        |
        v
    Clay (enrich via Claygent)
    - AI Initiatives signal
    - AI Leadership Hires signal
    - AI Success Stories signal
    - AI Partnerships signal
        |
        v
    Clay (score + tier)
    - Signal count, tier assignment
    - Primary angle selection
    - Research hook extraction
        |
        v
    Clay (generate copy)
    - LinkedIn connection request
    - Email Step 1 (initial)
    - Email Step 2 (follow-up)
        |
        v
    Clay (QA validation)
    - Dash check, sign-off check
    - Banned phrase check
    - Length and specificity check
        |
        +---> Clay Sequencer (email)
        |         |
        |         v
        |     Prospect inbox
        |
        +---> HeyReach (LinkedIn)
                  |
                  v
              LinkedIn
```

**Engagement loop:**
- Reply or LinkedIn acceptance triggers handoff notification to the founder
- Founder takes over conversation manually
- Deal created in vault, tracked through deal stages

## Email Infrastructure

| Setting | Value |
|---------|-------|
| Sender | founder@acme-consulting.com |
| Format | Plain text (HTML off) |
| Schedule | Mon-Fri, 9am-5pm ET |
| Daily limit | 20-30 sends |
| Min between sends | 20 minutes |

## Cost Considerations

Clay credits are the primary variable cost. Enrichment prompts (Claygent) consume the most credits because they fetch external data.

**Credit optimization:**
- Run company-level enrichment (AI positioning scan) once per unique company, copy results to all contacts
- Run person-level enrichment only on top-tier leads (score first with CSV data, then enrich A/B leads)
- Pre-written copy uses minimal credits (0.1 per email send)

## Tool Evaluation Notes

| Tool | Status | Notes |
|------|--------|-------|
| Clay | Active | Core platform, heavy usage |
| HeyReach | Active | LinkedIn automation |
| Sales Navigator | Active | Lead sourcing |
| HubSpot | Legacy | Data source only, not primary CRM |
| Google Sheets | Active | Analysis and sharing |
| Notion | Deprecated | Was used for tracking, replaced by vault |
